{
  "stem": "9665.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he said to me-- naturally, my father went with me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And my father spoke to him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There's no need for my son to go in the army.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The doctor said, if your son doesn't want to go to the army, I can fix that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Because he lost his son over London.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "He lost another son-- he had only two sons-- somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "London was the Battle of Britain.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, no, I said.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I want to join the army.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was arranged that my father should go to Curacao, and my mother-- during wartime this was all very complicated.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my mother would go from Suriname to Curacao that they should be together.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Suriname was rather difficult for them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, Bertha and Max Wolf and also from Suriname to Curacao.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I left Melitta in the camp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a camp, but it was an open camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a camp for refugees, but open.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The food was fantastic.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was even arranged that they could have kosher, not kosher.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I went to not kosher.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My father went for kosher.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were interrogated by an English intelligence serviceman who asked us how we got out of Holland.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And why did he ask us these questions?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because even with Jewish people, they were worried that there were some spies in between.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, they found a spy who was with us on the boat-- a Jewish man-- who was a cousin of the chief rabbi of The Hague who was jailed in Jamaica, and sent to England.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he finished up in the Isle of Man.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What happened to him later on-- I know the name of the man, but I don't want to put that in the video.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
